node.text:
We need 1 foot of water out of the lake immediately and also need to open up Cochran’s Pass to allow the 70,000 acres of Filter marsh to Breathe filtered water back Into Lake Okeechobee. Once the North of the Lake storage projects are complete this will help us store the water and slow the flow into the lake so we don’t kill our filter grasses in the rainy season.
.
.
Follow @anglersforlakeo @rolandmartinmarina #lakeokeechobee  #anglersforlakeokeechobee

node.text:
We are encouraging Gov. @rondesantisfl to fully fund the Storage North of the Lake project. This will help the overall water quality for the entire system. It will also help protect our natural grass filter that Lake Okeechobee needs to filter its own water everyday. Let’s get these projects going..we can’t wait any longer. .
.
Please check the link in my BIO and also let me know who checked it out...I want to personally say thank you! 🙏🏼 Follow us at @anglersforlakeo

node.text: Who’s going fishing this weekend? A lure to sling around in the dog days of summer is a very light or weightless Texas rigged worm. I personally like the 5” Googan Baits Lunker Log in GP color…it’s a absolute fish catcher! If you catch a fish be sure to tag me and I’ll drop it on my stories. Tag - @scottmartinchallenge 👊🏼

node.text:
There’s a lot of agony behind this smile…I worked extremely hard this week and lost the Classic Fish twice in the last 20m yesterday. I know there’s a reason above my understanding for the missed opportunities the last two weeks..so I am ok with that. I am so thankful for my family and all of the support and love they give me everyday and to you the fans for all of the encouragement you send my way! Love you guys! Videos coming soon.. @bass_nation 
.
.
There is a outside chance I could still qualify for the Classic through Open spots that aren’t used. 🙏🏼
